A mother and teenage son found dead in an apparent suicide have now been pictured for the first time.

Catherine Mhlaba is believed to have started a fire in her black Vauxhall Vectra, leading to her death as well as that of her disabled son Beki Ali.

The pair were found by police close to a yacht club in Southend-on-Sea on Tuesday evening, and emergency services were unable to save their lives.

