Mrs Mhalaba, 45, originally from Zimbabwe, was living in Shoeburyness at the time of her death and was an active member in the local Zimbabwean community.

She was caring for her 16-year-old son who had who had global delay, a condition which meant he had the mental age of a six-year-old.

Witnesses described seeing the car roll forwards as if it were being driven before it suddenly burst into flames.

'The investigation is currently looking at the possibility that Catherine Mhlaba was responsible for killing her son and taking her own life by starting the fire inside the car,' Chief Inspector Matt Bennett of Southend Police said.

